    "outcome": "success",
    "answer": "Based on my analysis of the codebase, here's what I've found:\n\n**Current behavior**: `ArchiveDayGrouping.HeadingFor()` returns only the day label (e.g. `\"Today\"`, `\"Yesterday\"`, or `\"dddd, MMMM d, yyyy\"`). Each `RelayTaskItem` has `CostUsd` (a `double`) and `MoneyFormatter.Dollars()` formats it (e.g. `\"$1.54\"`). The ViewModel sets `row.DayHeader` per row in a loop.\n\n**Key files involved**:\n- `src/VisualRelay.Core/Tasks/ArchiveDayGrouping.cs` \u2014 the pure helper that generates day headings\n- `src/VisualRelay.App/ViewModels/MainWindowViewModel.Helpers.cs` \u2014 caller that sets `DayHeader` line-by-line\n- `src/VisualRelay.Domain/RelayTaskItem.cs` \u2014 has `CostUsd` and `MoneyFormatter`\n- `tests/VisualRelay.Tests/ArchiveDayGroupingTests.cs` \u2014 tests to update\n\n---\n\n## Solution Options\n\n### Option A \u2014 Add a `dayTotalCost` parameter to `HeadingFor` + precompute in ViewModel\n\nPrecompute `Dictionary<DateOnly, double>` of day totals in the ViewModel's `ReloadTaskListAsync` (one pass through tasks, summing `CostUsd` per completion-day), then pass the relevant total into a new overload of `HeadingFor`:\n\n```csharp\npublic static string? HeadingFor(\n    IReadOnlyList<RelayTaskItem> orderedTasks, int index,\n    DateOnly today, double dayTotalCost)\n```\n\nThe method appends ` ($1.54)` to the heading when it returns non-null (only for the first row of each day). This keeps the formatting logic in the helper and the summation in the ViewModel.\n\n**Pros**: Single responsibility per layer; heading formatting stays in `ArchiveDayGrouping`; easy to test with the cost parameter.  \n**Cons**: Changes signature of an existing public method; ViewModel needs one extra loop to compute day totals.\n\n---\n\n### Option B \u2014 Append cost in the ViewModel only, keep `HeadingFor` unchanged\n\nIn `MainWindowViewModel.Helpers.cs`, after getting the heading from `HeadingFor`, compute the day's total cost inline and append it when the heading is non-null:\n\n```csharp\nif (ShowArchive)\n{\n    var heading = ArchiveDayGrouping.HeadingFor(tasks, i, today);\n    if (heading is not null)\n    {\n        var dayTotal = tasks\n            .Where(t => t.CompletedAt?.ToLocalTime().Date == tasks[i].CompletedAt?.ToLocalTime().Date)\n            .Sum(t => t.CostUsd);\n        row.DayHeader = $\"{heading} ({MoneyFormatter.Dollars(dayTotal)})\";\n    }\n    else\n    {\n        row.DayHeader = string.Empty;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Pros**: Minimal change \u2014 no new method/parameter, no test changes to `ArchiveDayGrouping` itself.  \n**Cons**: N+1 summation (re-summing the same day for each row); mixes formatting and grouping logic into the ViewModel; harder to unit-test the cost-in-heading format.\n\n---\n\n### Option C \u2014 Introduce a `HeadingForWithCost` helper that returns combined result\n\nAdd a new method to `ArchiveDayGrouping` that precomputes day totals and returns the heading with cost appended, plus a static helper to compute day totals:\n\n```csharp\n// New public method\npublic static string? HeadingWithCost(\n    IReadOnlyList<RelayTaskItem> orderedTasks, int index, DateOnly today)\n{\n    // compute dayTotal from orderedTasks grouped by completion day\n    // if first-of-day, return \"Today ($1.54)\" etc.\n    // otherwise null\n}\n\n// Helper exposed for testing\npublic static IReadOnlyDictionary<DateOnly, double> ComputeDayTotals(\n    IReadOnlyList<RelayTaskItem> orderedTasks)\n```\n\n**Pros**: Clean, testable, no changes to the original `HeadingFor` signature; ViewModel stays simple.  \n**Cons**: More new code; duplicates some grouping logic already in `HeadingFor`.\n\n---\n\n```json\n{\n  \"summary\": \"The archive day-group headings (\\\"Today\\\", \\\"Yesterday\\\", etc.) need to include the summed cost of all tasks completed that day, e.g. \\\"Today ($1.54)\\\". Each RelayTaskItem already carries CostUsd and MoneyFormatter.Dollars() formats it. Three approaches are viable: (A) add a dayTotalCost param to HeadingFor + precompute in ViewModel, (B) append cost in the ViewModel only, or (C) create a new HeadingWithCost method in ArchiveDayGrouping that precomputes day totals internally.\",\n  \"options\": [\n    \"Option A \u2014 Add `dayTotalCost` parameter to `HeadingFor`; ViewModel precomputes day totals dict\",\n    \"Option B \u2014 Append cost string in the ViewModel call-site, keep `HeadingFor` unchanged\",\n    \"Option C \u2014 New `HeadingWithCost()` method in `ArchiveDayGrouping` that computes day totals and formats combined heading\"\n  ]\n}\n```",
